Question: Do you have any additional ideas, concerns, or feedback you would like to share to help ACME better serve the public?

Response ID: resp_3249
Response Text: Just to repeat for emphasis - Trying to focus on highlighting Austin's fine artists over national/regional artists is provincial and backwards thinking. For music, I think it makes sense to focus on local artists because of the city's music and live performance history is superior to most other cities. For fine and cultural arts it's provincial to focus on Austin's fine arts community because it's substandard borderline amateurish compared to Houston, San Antonio and Dallas fine arts communities, let alone Chicago, Los Angeles, Atlanta, San Francisco, Boston, or New York City. I recently travelled through Bush International Airport in Houston. The City had an airport arts program in partnership with local museums/fine arts organizations. The fine art (sculptures, photographs, murals, paintings) displayed was comprised of artists from across the U.S. and the world (if I remember correctly) and NOT comprised of Houston only artists. In fact, I can't recall a single Houston-based artwork. And the art was EXCELLENT and a world class representation of the fine art available in Houston. Austin's fine arts can't match the competition. And that's ok. Focus on our strengths - music and live music performance.

